# Cloudflare Pages routing rules. Evaluated top-to-bottom; first match wins.
# Real files on disk are ALWAYS served before these rules, but we add an
# explicit well-known passthrough as belt-and-braces so the SPA catch-all can
# never swallow the App Links / Universal Links association files.

# Never SPA-rewrite the association files — they must return their real JSON.
/.well-known/*        /.well-known/:splat        200

# Everything else falls through to the Flutter SPA so GoRouter can handle the
# path client-side (deep links: /store/:id, /product/:id, /post/:id, etc.).
/*                    /index.html                200